les\n  return personalized if personalized\nend\n```\n\nThe rest of the method is unchanged (existing logic becomes the fallback).\n\n### 2. New private method `personalized_articles`\n\n```ruby\ndef personalized_articles\n  feed_config = FeedConfig.order(feed_success_score: :desc).first\n  return nil unless feed_config\n\n  set_subforem_context  # sets @subforem_ids and @skip_subforem_filtering\n\n  score_sql = feed_config.score_sql(@user)\n\n  articles_query = Article\n    .select(:title, :description, :path, :cached_user, :cached_tag_list,\n            :subforem_id, :comment_score, :comments_count)\n    .published\n    .full_posts\n    .where(\"published_at > ?\", cutoff_date)\n    .where(email_digest_eligible: true)\n    .not_authored_by(@user.id)\n    .order(Arel.sql(\"#{score_sql} DESC\"))\n    .limit(RESULTS_COUNT)\n\n  articles_query = articles_query.where(subforem_id: @subforem_ids) unless @skip_subforem_filtering\n\n  articles = articles_query.to_a\n  articles.length >= 3 ? articles : nil\nrescue StandardError\n  nil\nend\n```\n\nReturning `nil` (not an empty array) signals \"try fallback\" to the caller. Returning an array of < 3 articles also returns `nil`. An exception is silently swallowed and also returns `nil`.\n\n### 3. Regression specs to add\n\nAdd a new `context \"with personalized selection via FeedConfig\"` block inside `describe \"#articles_to_send\"`:\n\n- **Happy path**: FeedConfig exists → articles selected using personalized scoring are returned (>= 3).\n- **Fallback on empty personalized result**: FeedConfig exists but produces < 3 eligible articles → falls back to existing logic and returns legacy articles.\n- **Fallback on exception**: `FeedConfig#score_sql` raises → falls back to legacy selection.\n- **No FeedConfig**: `FeedConfig.order(...).first` returns `nil` → falls back to legacy selection.\n- **Existing guardrails preserved**: user's own article never appears; non-eligible articles excluded.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. **Unit tests**: `bundle exec rspec spec/services/email_digest_article_collector_spec.rb`\n2. **Manual smoke test (console)**:\n   ```ruby\n   user = User.find(<id>)\n   EmailDigestArticleCollector.new(user, force_send: true).articles_to_send\n   # Expect 3–7 articles personalized to the user\n   ```\n3. **Fallback verification**: Temporarily `FeedConfig.delete_all` in console; confirm articles are still returned via legacy path.\n4. **Exception fallback**: Stub `FeedConfig#score_sql` to raise; confirm legacy path kicks in.\n",
